# Versioning and commits

## Version files

On every release-worthy change, bump `BUILD_VERSION` (server/UI).

Bump `AGENT_VERSION` **only** when the **Linux or Windows agent** changes:

- `client/linux/` (e.g. `collect_and_send.sh`, `self_update.sh`, …)
- `client/windows/` (e.g. `collect_and_send.ps1`, `collect_and_scan_sap_tables.ps1`, …)
- mirrored agent payloads under `/updates` when those files change

Server/UI-only changes, other `client/` tooling, or docs: leave `AGENT_VERSION` unchanged.

`BUILD_VERSION` and `AGENT_VERSION` may diverge (e.g. BUILD `1.7.491`, AGENT `1.7.490`). Do not bump `AGENT_VERSION` just to keep them in sync.

When Windows agent scripts change, also sync embedded fallback:

- `client/windows/collect_and_send.ps1` → `$EmbeddedAgentVersion`
- `client/windows/collect_and_scan_sap_tables.ps1` → `$EmbeddedAgentVersion`

## Commit message format

Use the project prefix **`vX.Y.Z:`** at the start of the subject line (not `(v1.7.x)` at the end).

Good:

```
v1.7.344: fix ANG log viewer splitting merged tail lines
```

Bad:

```
Fix ANG log viewer (v1.7.344).
Bump AGENT_VERSION to 1.7.343
```

Body (optional) explains why; subject stays short with the version prefix.
